I) something done (usually as opposed to something said)
II) the state of being active
III) a military engagement
IV) a process existing in or produced by nature (rather than by the intent of human beings)
V) the series of events that form a plot
VI) the trait of being active and energetic and forceful
VII) the operating part that transmits power to a mechanism
VIII) a judicial proceeding brought by one party against another; one party prosecutes another for a wrong done or for protection of a right or for prevention of a wrong
IX) an act by a government body or supranational organization
X) the most important or interesting work or activity in a specific area or field

Do not provide explanations. Just output the choice.
RESULT:  The correct sense of the word "action" in the given text is:

I) something done (usually as opposed to something said)
The answer is: I
Gold answer is: 9
Attempted: 107, Correct: 60, Accuracy: 0.5607476635514018

IV) a summary of the subject or plot of a literary work or play or movie

 While the Europe and world champions , number one one in the monthly top of FIFA , have a long record of Class A inter selection , the Tricolor has only the defender Michael Umana as the only one who has 50 international games .


Do not provide explanations. Just output the choice.
RESULT:  B) The correct sense for the word "number one" in the given text is "rank" or "position".
PROMPT: Which of the following senses is correct for the word "top" in the following text:

II) the highest or uppermost side of anything
III) the top or extreme point of something (usually a mountain or hill)
IV) the first half of an inning; while the visiting team is at bat
V) the highest level or degree attainable; the highest stage of development
VI) the greatest possible intensity
VII) platform surrounding the head of a lower mast
VIII) a conical child's plaything tapering to a steel point on which it can be made to spin
IX) covering for a hole (especially a hole in the top of a container)
X) a garment (especially for women) that extends from the shoulders to the waist or hips
XI) a canvas tent to house the audience at a circus performance

Do not provide explanations. Just output the choice.
RESULT:  The correct sense of the word "top" in the given text is:

II) the highest or uppermost side of anything
The answer is: II
Gold answer is: 5

I) a person who participates in or is skilled at some game
II) someone who plays a musical instrument (as a profession)
III) a theatrical performer
IV) a person who pursues a number of different social and sexual partners simultaneously

Do not provide explanations. Just output the choice.
RESULT:  I
The answer is: I
Gold answer is: 1
Attempted: 1208, Correct: 793, Accuracy: 0.6564569536423841

RESULT:  The correct sense of the word "pound" in the given text is:
